name: paper production, newsprint, virgin | paper, newsprint | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3123/documentation

This dataset represents the European production of newsprint paper without the use of deinked pulp (DIP) from waste paper.;Principal sources for the dataset of Newsprint paper produced in Europe are the Finnish EcoData data-base from KCL (KCL (2002)), the report of the Swedish EPA about the Swedish pulp and paper in-dustry (Naturvardsverket (2001)) as well as several environmental reports from European paper mills (Hylte Mill (2000; Kvarnsveden Mill (2002; Sachsen Mill (2002; Summa Mill (2001)). Further sources are the German inventory study about graphical paper (Tiedemann et al. (2000)) of UBA, dis-tinguishing beteween a nordic and a German newsprint paper, a recently established study from EMPA comparing printed with electronic media (Reichart & Hischier (2001)) - including datasets from several newsprint paper mills - and the European IPPC documentation for the paper and pulp in-dustry (European Commission (2000)). In the latter one, besides BAT technology, the present situa-tion of the pulp and paper industry is described and quantified.;Further documentation about the background data to this dataset can be found in the report Hischier (2007), available through the ecoinvent online for v2.;Reference(s):;">> KCL (2002) KCL EcoData - life cycle inventory database. The Finnish Pulp and Paper Research Institute (KCL), Espoo (Finnland) <<;;>> Naturvardsverket (2001) Skogsindustrins utsläpp - avfallsmängder och energiförbrukning 2000. Report 5154. Naturvardsverket (Swedish EPA), Stockholm <<;;>> Hylte Mill (2000) Environmental Report 1999. StoraEnso Newsprint, Hyltebruk (Sweden) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2395-2103-,00.html <<;;>> Kvarnsveden Mill (2002) Environmental Report 2001. StoraEnso Kvarnsveden AB, Borlänge (Sweden) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2395-2103-,00.html <<;;>> Sachsen Mill (2002) Environmental Statement Sachsen Mill 2001. StoraEnso Sachsen GmbH, Eilenburg (Germany) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2394-2102-,00.html <<;;>> Summa Mill (2001) Environmental Statement Summa Mill 2000. Stora Enso Newsprint, Hamina (Finland) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2393-2097-,00.html <<;;>> Tiedemann A., Böttcher Tiedemann C., Buschardt A., Georgi B., Giersberg G., Goosmann G., Gregor H.-D., Mehlhorn B., Modi A., Neitzel H., Oels H.-J., Schmitz S. and Suhr M. (2000) Ökobilanzen für graphische Papiere. Texte 22/00. Umweltbundesamt, Berlin <<;;>> Reichart I. and Hischier R. (2001) Vergleich der Umweltbelastungen bei Benut-zung elektronischer und gedruckter Medien. EMPA-Bericht Nr. 253. EMPA, St. Gallen <<;;>> Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings and Graphical Papers. ecoinvent-Report No. 11, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007. <<;"

This activity starts with the reception of wood chips and other raw materials at the factory gate.

This activity includes the European production of newsprint paper without the use of deinked pulp (waste paper) - including transports to paper mill, wood handling, mechanical pulping and bleaching, paper production, energy production on-site and internal waste water treatment.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from a finnish database and from several European newsprint producers used as European average data.
